  • The validator currently treats value sets that contain exclude elements as ones where a code system cannot be determined. However, that's not appropriate. So long as there's only one include for the value set, the presence of excludes are irrelevant. For example, I have a value set that includes all specializations of code X, then explicitly excludes code X. There's only one include and only one system, so it's a perfectly appropriate value set to be bound to a 'code' extension. Stripping out the test that checks for excludes as irrelevant. (f6a5217)
